\par \plain\f2\fs16\b How to:
\par \pard\li200\fi-200{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent200{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs16 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}To add files, you can click on the checkmarks in front of a folder in the tree. If the folder is not expanded, all files (including the ones in subfolders) will be added. If the folder is expanded, just the contents of this one folder is added. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}See what is in a folder by selecting it. If the folder is not expanded, you will also see the contents of all subfolders.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}You can also look at the complete list of selected files by clicking on "All Items in Current Collection".
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}This list you can search and filter in any way. Rightclick your mouse on it and select one of the available filters.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs16 
\par \plain\f2\fs16\b Checking for duplicates:
\par \pard\li200\fi-200{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent200{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs16 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Click on the little "find duplicates" icon.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Wait for the filter to do it's work. You can see the progress in the status bar. When reaching 100%, all files are checked for duplicates.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Beware! The list shown contains duplicates AND originals! ABC-View Manager obviously does not know which is which so displays both (or three or four, etc, if there are more than two).
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Right click in the resulting list and click "Select ->  Select Duplicates". This will insure that you leave at least one original. The file that is not selected is the first one encountered of each group of duplicates.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Example: you want to keep the oldest files as originals: first sort the list from old to new. Then, click "Select" -> "Select Duplicates". The newer dupes are selected. Click the "Delete" icon to start the deletion process.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs16\b 
