\par \plain\f2\fs16\b Features present:
\par \pard\li200\fi-200{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent200{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs16 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Browse your folders, and select the ones you want to add to the database collection easily by checking them. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}View up to 1 Million items at once in a list. View them as list, small icons, large icons or thumbnails (resizable) in a modern browser. Memory management and components are all focused on performance. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Sort items on name, date, size, folder, series, rating, etc. The sorting algorithm is the fastest available (quicksort), and it uses fast binary compare methods. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Randomize items in the list (ultra-fast). This means that you can still use the normal "forward" and "backward" buttons in the slideshow, even on randomized items. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Scan for files across directories, this allows you to add your collection of files very easily. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Views all major types of files: JPEG, GIF, PNG, TIF, BMP and many others. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Enlarge or shrink your images to fit the screen size. This is done in a very friendly way, by first doing a quick resize and then using a background process to enhance the picture using Lazcos filtering. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Check for duplicates in the file list. This duplicate checker is one of the fastest around, and can be started in the background while working with the program. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Delete files safely and efficiently. Or move the files to an archive folder or a ZIP file. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Load and save your catalog files. Loading a catalog is usually much faster than actually scanning the files using explorer. The items are stored very efficiently using compression. No database is used, but an internal proprietary memory-efficient structure. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Drag/drop support to and from explorer. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Shell-notify (whenever changes occur in a folder these changes are updated automatically when ABC-View runs)
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Losless rotation, flipping and cropping of JPEG files by using lowlevel operations on the JPEG's structure. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Email the selected files directly from the application. Auto-shrink the images before sending. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Filter the items you want to see, filter by file type, file size, file date and many other criteria. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}"Build-a-Web" now functional!
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Delete files safely. Each time you are about to delete files, ABC-View Manager will prompt you with a dialog that contains information about your set of selected files. You can opt to put the files in the recycle bin (default) or into a ZIP archive or folder, or to delete the files without backup option.
